					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85085046" rend="visible">
						<summary>A book of short musarim, or ethical discourses, on the pericopes of the Pentateuch, composed in Italian by Isaac Lampronti, and translated into Hebrew by his pupils.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he"/>
						<msItem n="0" rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85085046">
							<locus from="1r" to="216v"/>
							<title xml:lang="ita">Documenti insegnati </title>
							<author key="http://viaf.org/viaf/55627259">
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/55627259" xml:lang="en">Lampronti, Isaac Hezekiah ben Samuel, 1679-1756 </persName>
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/55627259" xml:lang="he">לאמפרונטי, יצחק בן שמואל </persName>
							</author>
							<note>
								<p>Folio 1r is a title page.</p>
								<p>At the end of the various musarim there are the signatures of Lampronti's pupils, in their Hebrew and Italian names.</p>
								<p>Letters in Italian, relating to the death of Yosef Ḥayim, and to other subjects are found on folios 61, 62, 111, 112, 115.</p>
								<p>There are two Hebrew letters on folios 113-114 composed by pupils of Isaac Lampronti.</p>
								<p>Folios 58v-60v, 63v-69v, 117v, 159r-160v and 214-215 are occupied with shorter exercises in translation from Italian into Hebrew.</p>
								<p>The whole volume is planned as a book of exercises in Hebrew composition.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
